							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Being a new Brigand (main is a 42 Shadowknight) I'm somewhat confused by things I have read regarding the combat revamp.  I see people say we are losing our Feign Death, but I'm not sure exactly what that means.   I just recently got the Ruse CA, which appears to FD, but it says it has a 0% chance, then it does a huge amount of damage.  Is this the skill people are referring to as being removed in the revamp?  If so, is it only the FD part or does it not do much damage either?  What good news is there?  It seems the Predator subclasses and the Bard subclasses got alot of love, but I hardly see anything about the Rogue subclasses except that we can't use a bow with ranged CA's and something about feign death.
<br />

<br />
Any insights would be helpful, thank you.<br />_________________<br />Fingal Runesong
<br />
Dirge of Secret Keepers
<br />
Antonia Bayle</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Graeth on Sat Aug 27, 2005 11:20 am; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
