						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Graeth... you're 100% correct.  Ruse is only good for solo'ing now.  Using it in groups would be a newbie-ish thing to do.  Brigands don't want aggro in groups since all of our abilities are offensive.
<br />

<br />
No one who knows EQ hops on the adds unless the healer is in immediate risk of death.  Adds are for your crowd control specialist to deal with, your job is to apply as much damage to the #1 mob as possible.  Leave the others be...
<br />

<br />
Many priests I know just let the toons who pull aggro off the tank simply die and eventually the adds wander back to the tank.  So all those power nukers out there who chain nuke with no regard to aggro are at the mercy of the priest, who must decide if they want to waste power on a toon who keeps picking up aggro.
<br />

<br />
I think it's great that they nerfed our best CA down to the point of worthlessness.  A frontal attack that guarantees aggro on a toon without the ability to solo or mitigate damage properly... in a game that discourages solo'ing and forces group-based play by cranking up the aggro range, speed, damage potential, and mitigation of 100% of the mobs.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
					</table></td>
				</tr>
