						<tr>
							<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I'm a lvl 55 brig and before the expansion was really starting to lose patients with how boring being a brig could be .. barly able to solo. and most groups just wanted me around for invis. 
<br />

<br />
All though the loss of our FD ( lie low ) not even sure if thats what it was called now, has really put me in alot of bad situations, the improvement to our ruse has ultimitly made up for it.  
<br />

<br />
Has no one noticed that if you approach a group of mobs and position yourself just perfect while invised and then pop your ruse, instead of pulling the mobs you can hit every mob in the group ??  Some you will even get a dble on if they happen to hit you with a dble attack that lands at the same time??
<br />

<br />
This skill can do an extreme amount of damage to solo mob groups. You just have to play with how you execute it. 
<br />

<br />
If you havn't tried this , give it a whirl . you may be suprised how useful this skill is . As far as using it in a group you have to be quick. We all get agro off the tank at some point, to deni that is just lieing. If you pay attention you can pop off over 2k damage before the tank even knows he lost agro. With the new anti agro buff you have about 2 hits coming before the mob turns away... usually just one. 
<br />

<br />
As far as amazing reflexes goes, its unreal in a Named encounter with a mob that aes stun or the like, try it out in stormfeather's roost. Us brigs are the only melee to keep on swinging, and in that case stunning the mob so no one dies while the group just sits there and drools. =)</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
						</tr>
